sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.persistence.data

Class AbstractListenerRegistration

  • java.lang.Object
    • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.persistence.data.AbstractListenerRegistration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ListenerRegistration, Registration
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ListenerPersistenceData, LiveListenerRegistration

    public abstract class AbstractListenerRegistration
extends java.lang.Object
implements ListenerRegistration
    An abstract implementation of the ListenerRegistration interface. Implemented predicates like the current registration status are obtained directly from the core using the underlying listener or listener's data.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell

        public final boolean equals(@Nullable
             java.lang.Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this listener registration for equality. Returns true if the specified object is also a listener registration and the two registrations have the same listener implementation class. This definition ensures that this method works properly across different implementations of the listener registration interface.
